This is my own Gentoo overlay.


== Setup

One way to make use of the overlay is via 'layman' [1].
- Copy overlay.xml into /etc/layman/overlays/
- Uncomment the 'overlay_defs : /etc/layman/overlays' line in /etc/layman/layman.cfg
- Run 'layman -f; layman -a vooteys-overlay'
After executing these steps the overlay is ready to use.
More information about overlays and/or layman can be found here [2] and here [3].


[1] http://layman.sourceforge.net/
[2] http://en.gentoo-wiki.com/wiki/Overlay
[3] http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/overlays/userguide.xml